# AI Lab Manual Assistant – Week 4

## Internship
Saksham Agentic AI Internship

## Project Description
In Week 4, we improved the AI Lab Manual Assistant by implementing a retrieval-based question answering system. The system reads lab manual PDFs, converts the content into embeddings, and retrieves the most relevant information to answer user questions.

## Work Done This Week
- Implemented a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach
- Extracted text from uploaded lab manual PDFs
- Split the text into smaller chunks for processing
- Generated embeddings using Gemini API
- Stored embeddings in a FAISS vector database
- Retrieved relevant content to answer user questions
- Added support for multiple PDF uploads

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Google Generative AI (Gemini)
- FAISS
- PyPDF
- Google Colab

## How the System Works
1. User uploads one or more lab manual PDFs.
2. The system extracts text from the PDFs.
3. The text is split into smaller chunks.
4. Embeddings are generated for each chunk.
5. FAISS stores the embeddings for similarity search.
6. When a user asks a question, the system retrieves the most relevant chunks.
7. Gemini generates an answer using the retrieved context.

